<TITLE> 28 fishermen missing in Bay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barguna, May 27 (bdnews24.com)  At least 28 fishermen were missing as two trawlers sank in the Bay of Bengal in a storm near Laldia of Barguna Wednesday night. FB Mawla and FB Maa sank when a storm swept over the Bay suddenly at around 10pm, Golam Mostafa Chowdhury, District Trawler Owners' Association president, told bdnews24.com Thursday. Besides, locals rescued 36 fishermen of five other trawlers, which also sank in the storm. The five others FB Rahim, FB Alamgir, FB Badol, FB Monu and FB Jahangirsank in the Bishkhali river near Tetulbaria. Patharghata Upazila Nirbahi Officer Md Sohrab Hossain said, "I've heard of the two trawlers which sank with 28 fishermen." Rescue operations are under way, he added. bdnews2
